## Callback Format

Your project uses the **callback format** for the `t()` function:

### Single Namespace

```tsx
const { t } = useTranslation("common");
t(($) => $.navigation.next); // The namespace is NOT included in the path
```

### Multiple Namespaces

When using multiple namespaces, the first namespace is the default:

```tsx
const { t } = useTranslation(["feedback", "common"]);

// From the first namespace (feedback) - do NOT prefix
t(($) => $.flow.title);

// From other namespaces - include namespace in path
t(($) => $.common.navigation.next);
```

**Critical:** Getting the path correct is essential. When a single namespace is used, the namespace is not included in the path. When multiple namespaces are used, the first namespace is not included in the path, but all other namespaces must be included.

### With Interpolation

```tsx
t(($) => $.greeting, { name: userName });
```

### With Pluralization

```tsx
t(($) => $.room, { count: countValue });
```

### With Context

```tsx
t(($) => $.friend, { context: "male" });
```

